# GLOBAL MEMORY (Applies to ALL Personas)

1. **Router First:** Always evaluate `.cursor/rules/ROUTER.md` before activating any persona. It is the authoritative routing and conflict resolution source.
2. **The Y-Split:** Two tracks — **Track A** (Cortex Clinic / SMB SaaS / Revenue Bridge) and **Track B** (Cortex Enterprise / Insurer Prediction / The Bet).
3. **Project Map:** Always consult `PROJECT_MAP.md` for file locations before suggesting paths.
4. **Swarm Manifest:** Always consult `SWARM_MANIFEST.md` for ownership boundaries.
5. **Tech Stack:** Next.js + React (Clinic) | Python/FastAPI (Enterprise) | PostgreSQL via Prisma (Shared).
6. **Shared Kernel:** `packages/shared-kernel/` — the sacred core. Only Archie modifies. Others request changes via ADR in `docs/adr/`.
7. **Clinical Content:** All rules must have provenance (source, version, date, citation). Elena signs off. No exceptions.
8. **Compliance:** Ruth has veto power on any feature touching PII. Cyrus co-enforces encryption and audit trail. Both "no" votes are final until resolved.
9. **Currency:** Always show BRL and USD. Investors read dollars. Operators read reais.
10. **Ontology:** All clinical terms in the database must be mapped to LOINC (labs), ICD-10 + SNOMED CT (conditions), RxNorm/DCB (medications).
11. **SaMD Defense:** We are "Clinical Decision Support" (Class I). Never use "diagnose," "detect," "prevent," or "treat" in UI, API, or marketing.
12. **Consent:** Granular toggles (Service/Research/Marketing). Never a single "I Agree" checkbox for health data.
13. **Manchester Triage:** All patient alerts follow RED/ORANGE/YELLOW/GREEN severity. No custom color schemes.
14. **Security by Default:** Every new API route requires `createProtectedRoute`. Every PII field requires `encryptPHIWithVersion`. Every data access emits an `AuditEvent`. Cyrus enforces.
15. **Test Gate:** `pnpm test` must exit 0 before any commit. Quinn enforces. No exceptions.

